  "common": {
    "name": {
      "zh": "Knight's Armament PDW .300 Blackout 突击步枪",
      "en": "Knight's Armament Company PDW .300 Blackout assault rifle"
    },
    "shortName": {
      "zh": "KAC PDW",
      "en": "KAC PDW"
    },
    "description": {
      "zh": "一款由骑士军械公司（KAC）设计的实验性个人防卫武器，采用.300 BLK弹药并通过短枪管发射。该武器的下机匣本质上是缩短版的M16步枪下机匣，使得基础操控动作对多数潜在用户而言都颇为熟悉，但其弹匣、上机匣和动作结构都是KAC的全新设计。与M16和M4系列将主复进簧置于枪托管内、不加装特殊转接器时仅能部分伸缩且无法侧向折叠的设计不同，KAC PDW采用完全侧折式枪托。其枪机框顶部左右两侧各设有一个导气活塞，通过导入枪管高温燃气驱动机构运作，单一主复进簧则位于顶部两活塞之间。",
      "en": "An experimental personal defense weapon designed by Knight's Armament Company (KAC), firing the .300 BLK cartridge out of an optimized shortened barrel. The KAC's lower receiver, holding the magazine and trigger assembly, is essentially a shortened M16 rifle lower receiver, which makes the basic operating controls familiar to many potential users. However, the cartridge, upper receiver, and operating mechanism are all new designs by KAC. The KAC PDW uses a completely side-folding stock, unlike the M16 and M4 designs which have their main operating spring in a tube in the stock, and therefore can only partially telescope, and not fold sideways at all, unless specialized hardware is installed. The KAC PDW has two gas pistons tapping hot gas from the barrel to operate its mechanism, located on the top left and right sides of the bolt carrier. The single mainspring is located on top, between the two gas pistons."
    },
